  "text": "Golgi bodies in A. baicalensis are located only on one side of the nucleus which turns to the cell periphery. The same arrangement of Golgi bodies is described for Melosira varians Agardh [CITATION_1] from the closely-related order of the same class Coscinodiscophyceae.",
